emancipata est z primarily a legal expression. emancipe meant strictly to put a son out of the hand and power of the father. This was accomplished at first by three fictitious sales; in later times by a simple declaration before the proper magistrate. emancipe was also used in a wider sense to denote the transfer of ownership in property from one person to another. Again, it was employed, apart from its legal significance, in the general sense of giving up, or surrendering something to another.
